title: File:U.S. Navy Capt. Cathal O'Connor, second from left, the commodore of Amphibious Squadron 11, points out landmarks of Darwin, Australia, to Seaman Dustin Johnson, third from left, and Seaman Brandyn McQuigg as 130828-N-KE519-021.jpg
author: MCSA Edward Guttierrez III
description: U.S. Navy Capt. Cathal O'Connor, second from left, the commodore of Amphibious Squadron 11, points out landmarks of Darwin, Australia, to Seaman Dustin Johnson, third from left, and Seaman Brandyn McQuigg as the forward-deployed amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6) makes a scheduled port visit to Darwin Aug. 28, 2013, while participating in exercise Koolendong 2013. Koolendong is an amphibious and live-fire exercise designed to increase interoperability between the U.S. Marine Corps and Australian Defence Force.
